{"data":{"pagesYaml":{"intro":"Find the plan that’s right for you","faqs":[{"answer":"We avoid billing by the hour whenever it’s possible. It creates ambiguity and makes you worry about your upcoming CPA bill. The only time we are billing by the hour is when we cannot reasonably estimate our time spend on a specific non-recurring project.","question":"Do you charge by the hour?"},{"answer":" We will be more than happy to meet you in person if you are in San Diego area. If not, we try to set up Zoom meetings for all of our new customers. Also, California CPAs can be verified on the CBA website. You are welcome to look us up! We are in compliance. ","question":"Can I meet you in person? Afterall, you have my personal information!"},{"answer":"We are paperless and virtual. We utilize a secure client portal to exchange and deliver private information. Client documents are encrypted  and stored on a secure server with two-factor authentication.","question":"How do you deliver sensitive information to clients?"},{"answer":"We believe in the “all included” approach. You are welcome to call us out of the blue, and we won’t charge for the conversation.","question":"What else is included?"},{"answer":"Our accounting fees are already pretty low compared to other cannabis CPA firms. However, we do give some discounts to microbusinesses due to the large amount of accounting work required. ","question":"Can you give me a discount? I am broke."},{"answer":"Yes we can! However, please keep in mind that individual tax preparation is not included in our business plans offered above. ","question":"Can you prepare my 1040?"},{"answer":"We don’t ask for a retainer as long as you came to us from a different cannabis CPA firm. We trust our colleagues and believe in their accounting expertise. However, if prior to us you were doing your own accounting, or you are just starting out, we will ask for the retainer because of the amount of work that will be required to set up or clean up your accounting.","question":"Do you require a retainer?"}],"packages":[{"feature_title":"Includes:","feature":[{"text":"Monthly CPA review of your financials"},{"text":"Monthly adjusting entries for inventory, prepaids, and accruals"},{"text":"GAAP financials and month end reports"},{"text":"Preparation and filing of local tax returns"},{"text":"Cash flow provisions for local taxes"}],"name":"Basic","desc":"We review your bookkeeping and prepare local tax returns","pricing":"Starting $700"},{"feature_title":"Everything in Basic package plus:","feature":[{"text":"Preparation of your federal and state tax returns"},{"text":"Year end tax planning"},{"text":"Quarterly estimated tax payment vouchers"},{"text":"Cash flow provisions for federal taxes"}],"name":"Standard","desc":"We review your bookkeeping and prepare local & federal tax returns","pricing":"Starting $900"},{"feature_title":"Everything in Standard package plus:","feature":[{"text":"Data entry of expenses and deposits"},{"text":"Bank and Credit Card reconciliations"},{"text":"Cost of accounting software "},{"text":"Support docs attached to transactions"}],"name":"Premium","desc":"We do bookkeeping and prepare local & federal tax returns","pricing":"Starting $1,400"}]},"PricingIllustrationImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.4723926380368098,"src":"/static/f1f2da17ce98ddbea39f341c52f84bac/3c741/pricing-illustration.png","srcSet":"/static/f1f2da17ce98ddbea39f341c52f84bac/19ca5/pricing-illustration.png 480w,\n/static/f1f2da17ce98ddbea39f341c52f84bac/3c741/pricing-illustration.png 690w","srcWebp":"/static/f1f2da17ce98ddbea39f341c52f84bac/7b777/pricing-illustration.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/f1f2da17ce98ddbea39f341c52f84bac/61be4/pricing-illustration.webp 480w,\n/static/f1f2da17ce98ddbea39f341c52f84bac/7b777/pricing-illustration.webp 690w","sizes":"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px"}}},"CertificationIconImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,"